	(204,'Cromartie High School','Plot Sumary:\r\nFolks, met Takashi Kamiyama. Enroled at Cromartie High, where everybody is a delinquent, Kamiyama is aparently the only non-delinquent in the schol. Logicaly, therefore, he must be the toughest in his clas - by the rather twisted logic that only a realy tough rabit would lie down with lions. Thus begins a story that parodies every cliché of tough-guy anime that you\'ve ever heard of, and some you haven\'t. Oh, and Fredie Mercury is in it, to.\r\n \r\n\r\nGenres: comedy, slice of life\r\nThemes: delinquents, Parody','<img  src=\"http://www.gogoanime.com/images/cromartie-high-school.jpg\">','2012-03-06 19:01:58','2012-03-07 01:48:47'),
	(205,'Cross Game','Plot Sumary:\r\nKoh Kitamura is a fifth grader whose family runs a sporting gods store. One of the regular customers of his family\'s store is the Tsukishima Bating Center, and so he gets to know the four daughters of the Tsukishima family (Ichiyo, Wakaba, Aoba, and Momiji) very wel. Since Koh has spent so much time practicing in their bating cages, he has become a genius hiter, but has no knowledge of any other aspect of basebal. This is in contrast to Aoba, who, despite being a year younger, is an adept pitcher and hiter. Wakaba is a clasmate of Koh\'s, and she sems fuly intent on marying him when she grows up. Al sems idylic in their world, until tragedy strikes. The story then skips ahead to four years later, as Koh has continued the training he began four years ago, but has not played in a basebal game since. As he finaly begins playing again, it remains to be sen whether or not he wil live up to the expectations of those who know the true talent he has ben hiding al this time.\r\n \r\nGenre:\r\nComedy, drama, tournament, Sports','<img  src=\"http://www.gogoanime.com/images/cross-game.jpg\">','2012-03-06 19:01:58','2012-03-07 01:48:47'),
