	(749,'Pokemon Season 13: Sinnoh League Victors','Plot Sumary:\r\nAs Ash and his friends continue their journey to Sunyshore City, they are atacked by a wild Magnezone. As they reach a near-by town, they are informed by Oficer Jeny that Magnezone and wild Metagros has sudenly apeared and is wreaking havoc throughout the town. As Pikachu and Pachirisu lead the Stel-types to the mountains using their Electric atacks, the group mets up with Katsuzou, a mountain guard. Then Katsuzou informs them that Magnezone and Metagros normaly batle with each other on a regular basis to release the magnetism that builds up in their bodies, due to the strong magnetic forces emited from the mountains. Recently, their “batle arena” (a dep crater) has become filed with water. Ash, Dawn, Brock, Oficer Jeny and Katsuzou have to find out why the crater is ful of water, and a way to drain it, so Magnezone and Metagros can batle in peace away from the city.','<img  src=\"http://www.gogoanime.com/images/pokemon-season-13-sinnoh-league-victors.jpg\">','2012-03-06 19:01:59','2012-03-07 02:05:35'),
	(750,'Pokemon Season 14: Black and White','Plot Sumary:\r\nPokémon: Black & White, the fourtenth season of the Pokémon anime television series, covering the continuing adventures of series protagonist Ash Ketchum as he travels to the new region of Unova. In Japan, this is the first portion of the Pocket Monsters: Best Wishes! branding of the anime series. Brock and Dawn have left the series, and Ash is joined by a new female trainer named Iris and a new male trainer named Cilan. The evil syndicate Team Rocket has a part to play in this season and the once comical members Jesie, James, and Meowth have ben promoted to a higher status and are in a more serious role.','<img  src=\"http://www.gogoanime.com/images/pokemon-season-14-black-and-white.jpg\">','2012-03-06 19:01:59','2012-03-07 02:05:36'),
